## OBS Studio Integration

Integrate Render Network's powerful tools with OBS Studio for seamless gamification and monetization. Transform your stream into an interactive experience with professional overlays and automated systems.

## Browser Source Setup

### Basic Integration

<Steps>
  <Step title="Add Browser Source">
    In OBS Studio, add a new Browser Source:

    **Source Configuration:**
    1. Click "+" in Sources panel
    2. Select "Browser Source"
    3. Name: "Render Network Overlay"
    4. Check "Create new" if needed
    5. Click "OK"

  </Step>

  <Step title="Configure Source Properties">
    Set up the browser source properties:

    **Properties Settings:**
    ```json
    {
      "URL": "https://555.rendernet.work/overlay",
      "Width": 1920,
      "Height": 1080,
      "FPS": 60,
      "CSS": "body { background: transparent !important; }",
      "ShutdownSource": true,
      "RestartWhenActivated": false
    }
    ```

  </Step>

  <Step title="Position & Scale">
    Position the overlay correctly in your scene:

    **Positioning Guide:**
    - **Bottom Third:** For chat and alerts
    - **Top Right:** For prediction markets
    - **Full Screen:** For mini-games
    - **Corner Overlays:** For persistent elements

  </Step>

  <Step title="Test Integration">
    Test the integration before going live:

    **Testing Checklist:**
    - ✅ Overlay loads without errors
    - ✅ Wallet connection works
    - ✅ Games appear correctly
    - ✅ Performance impact is minimal (<5% CPU)
    - ✅ Audio and video sync properly

  </Step>
</Steps>
